I"ø<h1 id="alert">Alert</h1>

<p>Use alerts to inform or warn users of a temporary situation that may impact  them accessing council services. They should be displayed at the top of the main body of content.</p>

<p>We have 3 types of alert that we use on the Essex County Council website (Essex.gov.uk)</p>

<ul>
  <li>the <a href="#information">information alert</a></li>
  <li>the warning alert</li>
  <li>the error alert</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="information">Information</h2>

<div class="alert info" id="tab-two">
  <div class="alert-icon">
    <span class="fas fa-info-circle"></span>
  </div>
  <div class="alert-text">
    <div class="section-heading">We are updating our system</div>
    <p>We have been doing lots of research and you have helped us update this service.</p>
    <button class="text" type="button" onclick="toggle_visibility('tab-two');">Hide this message</button>
  </div>
</div>

